sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as ML Model / Client
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS edge
    participant FS as Feature Server<br/>6566/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant SecMgr as SecurityManager<br/>(in-process)
    participant Online as Online Store<br/>(Redis 6379/TCP)
    participant Offline as Offline Store<br/>(BigQuery 443/TCP)
    participant Operator as Feast Operator<br/>8081/TCP
    participant Registry as Registry REST<br/>8001/TCP
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP

    Note over Client,Online: Flow 1: Online Feature Retrieval
    Client->>Route: POST /get-online-features<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (OIDC/K8s)
    Route->>FS: Forward (TLS terminated)<br/>6566/TCP
    FS->>SecMgr: Check permissions<br/>READ_ONLINE policy
    SecMgr-->>FS: Authorized
    FS->>Online: Read features<br/>TCP 6379, Password auth
    Online-->>FS: Feature values
    FS-->>Route: JSON Response
    Route-->>Client: Feature values

    Note over Client,Online: Flow 2: Feature Materialization (CronJob)
    Note right of Operator: CronJob triggers on schedule
    Operator->>FS: kubectl exec into pod<br/>ServiceAccount RBAC
    FS->>Offline: Read historical features<br/>HTTPS 443, GCP credentials
    Offline-->>FS: Feature data
    FS->>Online: Write materialized features<br/>TCP 6379, Password auth
    Online-->>FS: Write confirmed

    Note over Client,Online: Flow 3: Feature Push (with offline batching)
    Client->>Route: POST /push<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Route->>FS: Forward<br/>6566/TCP
    FS->>SecMgr: Check permissions<br/>WRITE_ONLINE / WRITE_OFFLINE
    SecMgr-->>FS: Authorized
    FS->>Online: Write features immediately
    Online-->>FS: Confirmed
    Note right of FS: Background thread batches<br/>offline writes (size + time flush)
    FS->>Offline: Batch write (async)<br/>HTTPS 443

    Note over Operator,K8sAPI: Flow 4: Operator Auto-Access RBAC
    Operator->>Registry: GET /api/v1/permissions<br/>8001/TCP, Intra-comm JWT
    Registry-->>Operator: Permission policies
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update RBAC resources<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS, SA token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: RBAC applied
